dx\;dy=r\;dr\;d\theta
(x,y)=(r\cos\theta,r\sin\theta)
\left|\frac{\partial (x,y)}{\partial(r,\theta)}\right|=\left|   \begin{array}{cc}     \frac{\partial x}{\partial r} & \frac{\partial x}{\partial \theta} \\     \frac{\partial y}{\partial r} & \frac{\partial y}{\partial \theta} \\   \end{array} \right|=\left|   \begin{array}{cc}     \cos\theta & -r\sin\theta \\     \sin\theta & r\cos\theta \\   \end{array} \right|=r,
dx\; dy=r\;dr\; d\theta.
